snippet: A long-sought suspect was nabbed, but another target eluded capture in raids by United States forces in North Africa over the weekend.
abstract: United States Navy SEAL teams, in separate weekend raids, capture Al Qaeda leader Nazih Abdul-Hamed al-Ruqai, better known as Abu Anas al-Libi, in Tripoli, Libya, but fail to seize Shabab operative in Somalia; disparate results in two corners of North Africa serve as reminder of uncertainties of warfare and limits of power even for one of America's most storied military units.

byline.original: By PETER BAKER and DAVID E. SANGER
byline.contributor: Reporting was contributed by Carlotta Gall from Tripoli, Libya; Nicholas Kulish from Nairobi, Kenya; Eric Schmitt from San Francisco; and Mark Mazzetti from Madrid.

lead_paragraph: A long-sought suspect was nabbed, but another target eluded capture in raids by United States forces in North Africa over the weekend.
